 the agent filter includes libraries but not test classes. If that’s the case, the native image run could fail due to missing metadata for those test classes. However, existing tests might already be covered because the TCK agent default includes them. I think the user filter captures all dynamic access for libraries, not tests. GraalVM still needs a reflection config for application classes.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9s9RyfnqqulikrBNTAu7ELvo|fc_034cbbecb2ce62c8016a2586f59f6081958071fac450ebb587", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    jvmArgs \"--add-opens=java.base/java.io=ALL-UNNAMED\"\n}\n", "newText": "tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    jvmArgs \"--add-opens=java.base/java.io=ALL-UNNAMED\"\n    jvmArgs \"--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED\"\n}\n"}, {"oldText": "        test {\n            buildArgs.add(\"--add-opens=java.base/java.io=ALL-UNNAMED\")\n        }\n", "newText": "        test {\n            buildArgs.add(\"--add-opens=java.base/java.io=ALL-UNNAMED\")\n            buildArgs.add(\"--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED\")\n        }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1360, "output": 1665, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46545, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780844240580, "responseId": "resp_034cbbecb2ce62c8016a2586d12e2481958dab2830ae21aecb"}}
