[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test execution in native image**\n\nI think tests should run under the native image by default. For XStream, the current SerializationMembersTest is using private test helper classes, and I guess it’s passing? But if the user-code-filter excludes test classes, I’m wondering if the TCK test infrastructure includes test class metadata. \n\nThere’s a possibility that existing tests pass because the native image can access app classes. I’ll need to consider how reflection config for private methods may play in, and if using public static proxies might help reduce access issues.\n\n**Examining native image metadata**\n\nI’m considering whether the native image includes metadata automatically for user code. I'm not completely sure! For dynamic-access coverage, metadata seems to apply mainly to library calls, and it looks like the agent filter includes libraries but not test classes. If that’s the case, the native image run could fail due to missing metadata for those test classes. However, existing tests might already be covered because the TCK agent default includes them. I think the user filter captures all dynamic access for libraries, not tests. GraalVM still needs a reflection config for application classes.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_034cbbecb2ce62c8016a2586d1e8c881958788049e6aeb5b0d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJYb1qeY0ZiLOlfnxcbJOJH4X74YFIHqHFMi_rTk3zmGroSjhu9ZCAmsExUDUAAnlFiEirRmuEewiqY-1749dISArfreb3dfERTVlYBrC_otvOboU4qQGS1N3489n69DGYcnXbdln_XqYgNtsXjUQV7snCKHn9WdfVBshoE2R314pxJcUph1haqPWVbT-8sp5BIDzYy84qx8eraf1Yg8vBilKgWraBK4r1NWFpRWeG6W9fCTOQn9geMfhNK5eFKwr3W-s9mrPKs7eDwCkjc1scskoJDvmODbeqNRSN6Rs01w_Ig-7nKHIjrPH_eZjygkMmFGZEPg-5oeQsNJ7vHnMcW8-px2YFiSdWB_yYlZHCXYoCA0IMV52FIK655iD4Ye4u3JyTjXJwexSlY8X29-VXTrYEvyox7FmaSyyOtIhsjM3aatirxLAzUL56JdrOQQdwgqHlMJcmr8JVaIojGjthdPJsEIIundk3sp1aB_bEWBrc